1Ô∏è‚É£ Inner Join
Q1. Retrieve all orders with customer names.
Tables: Orders(order_id, customer_id, amount) and Customers(customer_id, name)

Answer
sql
Copy code
SELECT o.order_id, c.name, o.amount
FROM Orders o
INNER JOIN Customers c
ON o.customer_id = c.customer_id;
2Ô∏è‚É£ Left Join
Q2. Get all customers and their orders, including customers with no orders.
Answer
sql
Copy code
SELECT c.customer_id, c.name, o.order_id, o.amount
FROM Customers c
LEFT JOIN Orders o
ON c.customer_id = o.customer_id;
3Ô∏è‚É£ Right Join
Q3. List all orders and customer names, including orders with missing customer info.
Answer
sql
Copy code
SELECT o.order_id, c.name, o.amount
FROM Orders o
RIGHT JOIN Customers c
ON o.customer_id = c.customer_id;
4Ô∏è‚É£ Full Outer Join
Q4. Show all customers and orders, matching where possible.
Answer (PostgreSQL / SQL Server)
sql
Copy code
SELECT c.customer_id, c.name, o.order_id, o.amount
FROM Customers c
FULL OUTER JOIN Orders o
ON c.customer_id = o.customer_id;
5Ô∏è‚É£ Self Join
Q5. Display employees and their managers from the Employees(emp_id, name, manager_id) table.
Answer
sql
Copy code
SELECT e1.name AS Employee, e2.name AS Manager
FROM Employees e1
LEFT JOIN Employees e2
ON e1.manager_id = e2.emp_id;
6Ô∏è‚É£ Cross Join
Q6. Show all combinations of products and categories.
Answer
sql
Copy code
SELECT p.product_name, c.category_name
FROM Products p
CROSS JOIN Categories c;
7Ô∏è‚É£ Join with WHERE filter
Q7. Get orders with amount > 500 and customer names.
Answer
sql
Copy code
SELECT o.order_id, c.name, o.amount
FROM Orders o
JOIN Customers c
ON o.customer_id = c.customer_id
WHERE o.amount > 500;
8Ô∏è‚É£ Using Aliases
Q8. Join tables with aliases for readability.
Answer
sql
Copy code
SELECT c.name AS CustomerName, o.amount AS OrderAmount
FROM Customers AS c
INNER JOIN Orders AS o
ON c.customer_id = o.customer_id;
9Ô∏è‚É£ Join multiple tables
Q9. Retrieve employee name, department name, and manager name.
Tables: Employees(emp_id, name, manager_id, dept_id) and Departments(dept_id, dept_name)

Answer
sql
Copy code
SELECT e.name AS Employee, d.dept_name, m.name AS Manager
FROM Employees e
JOIN Departments d ON e.dept_id = d.dept_id
LEFT JOIN Employees m ON e.manager_id = m.emp_id;
üîü Using JOIN with GROUP BY
Q10. Get total order amount for each customer.
Answer
sql
Copy code
SELECT c.name, SUM(o.amount) AS TotalAmount
FROM Customers c
JOIN Orders o ON c.customer_id = o.customer_id
GROUP BY c.name;
